Just to clarify - this original issue is caused by a version mismatch with the dev branch scripts and the formal pip release vxm package. Alternatively to @Hoda1394's recommendation, another option is to use the scripts from the master brach, which should always correspond to the most recent pypi release.

@tphankr regarding the above issue, you should first check to make sure your data is preprocessed in the same way described in the top-level readme (you can use the example OASIS dataset as a reference). If you still run into issues, it's probably best to open a new issue.
